Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling in the capacity determined by the department;
5) Spend twelve (12) months in jail; Nine (9) months up front, under the Huber Law including treatment, to commence on 04-03-15 by 6:00 p.m.  Three (3) months jail, stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion. 
6) Pay costs of action;
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
8) Provide DNA sample.   
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment.
$500.00 cash bail applied to court costs.    
Minutes.
